Package Controller

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAppointmentScreen
    This class allows the user to enter information into combo boxes and text fields in order to save them as an appointment in the database.
    AddCustomerScreen
    This class allows the user to enter information into combo boxes and text fields in order to save a new customer to the database
    AppointmentsController
    This class displays a table of appointment and has several buttons to allow for adding, editing, or deleting appointments.
    ContactScheduleController
    This class displays the appointments in a table that are associated with a contact that is selected by the user
    CustomersController
    This class displays the customers in a table and has various buttons to allow for adding, editing, and deleting customers
    EditAppointmentScreen
    This class allows the user to edit/modify an existing appointment that was selected in the table on the appointment screen.
    EditCustomerScreen
    This class allows the user to edit/modify an existing customer that was selected from the table on the customer screen.
    LoginPageController
    This class checks entered credentials to log into the application.
    MainScreenController
    This class has several buttons used to navigate to the main portions of the application.
    ReportsController
    This class has several buttons that allow the user to navigate to another screen depending on which report they would like to view.
    TotalAppointmentsController
    This class allows the user to generate a report of the amount of appointments by either month or type based on what customer they have selected.
